{
  "texts": [
    "Extreme weather conditions such as direct sunlight, rain, snow, or fog can significantly degrade LiDAR's detection performance [11,132].",
    "Considerable research has been dedicated to denoising weather-induced interferences to address this challenge due to extreme weather.",
    "Park et al. [105] propose a Low-Intensity Outlier Removal (LIOR) fil-123 ter to eliminate snow particles from the LiDAR point cloud.",
    "Utilizing a CNN-based approach, WeatherNet [49], a variant of LiLaNet [107], is trained with augmented data incorporating a fog model and a rain model.",
    "This training process aims to effectively remove noise caused by adverse weather conditions from the actual LiDAR data."
  ]
}